race.comment: THE CRIMSON PIRATE (4) just missed at the end of last campaign when a $1.30 favourite over 1400m at this track 70 days ago. His trial coming in was solid enough and Pike remains in the saddle from that trial. Looks to have found a suitable race first-up and can land the knockout blow. BONDI LIFESAVER (7) trialled well going into his debut performance and was strong late in the race over 1000m at Northam. Likely to get back in the run again from the barrier, though the extra furlong should suit and if he gets some luck in running, he'll be hard to hold out. REFEMME NO ANGEL (8) was only fair on debut but he looks to have gone to another level this time in work, winning his past two trials impressively. Now a gelding and with the winkers on, he can put his best foot forward on resumption. GABEX (11) wasn't beaten far on debut and is not to be discounted. OURGIRLCANRUN (9) was good off a short break last start and will appreciate this easier race today.
